name: Deviled Eggs with Dill and Prosciutto
author: Robnorth914
summary: These deviled eggs are a wonderful appetizer, with lots of fresh dill, plenty of spicy Dijon mustard, plus a surprise layer of prosciutto.
ingredients: 2 thin slices  prosciutto, or as needed
directions: Place eggs in a saucepan; cover with water
Bring to a boil, remove from heat, and let eggs stand in hot water for 15 minutes
Remove eggs from hot water, cool under cold running water, and peel
Cut each egg in half lengthwise; place egg yolks in a bowl
Mash yolks with a fork; stir in dill, mayonnaise, and Dijon mustard
Place egg whites cut-side-up on a serving platter
Cut each prosciutto slice into 6 pieces; lay one piece into each egg white half
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture; sprinkle with black pepper, top with a cucumber slice, and sprinkle with paprika
Refrigerate, covered, for 30 minutes before serving
